- VSCode Version: 1.12.0-insider
- OS Version: Linux Mint 18

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Paste this code:
```ts
class C {
    m() {
        if (true) {
            return;
        }
    }
}
```

2. `Ctrl-K`, `Ctrl-0` to collapse all.
3. Expand `class C`. (Do not expand the `m`.)
4. Click inside the parens in `m` and write `param: number`.
5. An extra `...` symbol appears in the middle of the inserted text.

![screenshot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/19274678/25410459/c2909e1c-29cb-11e7-8af1-d80112772460.jpg)

I am unable to debug Typescript files in Visual Studio Code. If I change program in ````launch.json```` to "program": "${workspaceRoot}/server/dist/server.js" I am able to get the debugger to debug the transpiled JavaScript files. I have pasted my launch.json, tsconfig.json, and directory structure below for your convenience. 

- VSCode Version: 1.11.2
- OS Version: Windows 10
- Node Version: 6.10.1

```launch.json```
```
{
    // Use IntelliSense to learn about possible Node.js debug attributes.
    // Hover to view descriptions of existing attributes.
    // For more information, visit: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=830387
    "version": "0.2.0",
    "configurations": [{
            "type": "node",
            "request": "launch",
            "name": "Debug Program",
            "program": "${workspaceRoot}/server/src/server.ts",
            "cwd": "${workspaceRoot}",
            "env": {
                "NODE_ENV": "development"
            },
            "skipFiles": [
                "node_modules/**/*.js"
            ],
            "outFiles": [
                "${workspaceRoot}/server/dist/**/*.js"
            ],
            "sourceMaps": true,
            "stopOnEntry": true,
            "console": "internalConsole",
            "trace": "all"
        },
        {
            "type": "node",
            "request": "attach",
            "name": "Attach to Port",
            "address": "localhost",
            "port": 5858,
            "outFiles": []
        }
    ]
}
 ````


```tsconfig.json```
```
{
    "compilerOptions": {
        "target": "es6",
        "module": "commonjs",
        "outDir": "dist",
        "sourceMap": true,
        "rootDir": "src"
    },
    "include": [
        "src/**/*.ts"
    ],
    "exclude": [
        "node_modules"
    ]
}
```

